// Semantic direction:
// scene_editor is the main editor application wrapping the game runtime.
// scene_hierarki shows the tree of entities and their parent/child relationships.
// hierarki_velg selects an entity, updating inspektør with its components.
// inspektør lists all components on the selected entity with editable fields.
// inspektør_rediger sends a command that updates the component field and records undo.
// transformasjon_widget renders 3D gizmos (arrows, rings, handles) over the selected entity.
// snap_til_rutenett rounds translate/rotate/scale to the nearest snap_verdi increment.
// scene_kamera is a free-flying editor camera independent of any in-game camera.
// undo_stack records editor_hendelse entries; undo pops and reverses; redo re-applies.
// prefab_editor opens a prefab in isolation; prefab_overskriv pushes changes to all instances.
// editor_play enters modus_spill: the runtime advances, but state resets on editor_stopp.
// editor_steg advances exactly one frame then pauses — useful for frame-by-frame debugging.

// Primitive flow:
// select entity: klikk i hierarki -> hierarki_velg(eid) -> valgt_entitet = eid
//   -> inspektør.vis(eid) -> hent alle komponenter -> render felt per komponent
// edit field: inspektør_rediger(eid, komponent, felt, ny_verdi)
//   -> undo_stack.push(gammel_verdi) -> anvend ny_verdi -> oppdater scene
// undo: undo_stack.pop -> reverser hendelse -> redo_stack.push
// gizmo drag: transformasjon_widget fanger musedrag -> beregn delta i 3D-rom
//   -> snap? -> avrund delta -> inspektør_rediger(transform.posisjon, ny_pos)
// play: editor_play -> serialisér scene_tilstand -> start spill_løkke
//   -> editor_stopp -> deserialiser scene_tilstand -> gjenopprett editor

// This defines the scene editor: entity hierarchy, component inspector,
// transform gizmos, undo/redo, prefab editing, and play/pause/step modes.

