// Semantic direction:
// script_sandbox is an isolated execution environment for untrusted Norscode scripts.
// sandbox_motor is the underlying VM instance with restricted module access.
// kontekst_isolert prevents scripts from accessing the host application's state directly.
// innfødt_binding exposes selected host functions to the sandbox via api_eksponér.
// script_kompiler compiles script_kilde to script_bytekode within the sandbox boundary.
// kompiler_inkrementell reuses prior bytecode for unchanged top-level declarations.
// hot_patch replaces a running function's bytecode without restarting the sandbox.
// patch_diff computes the minimal bytecode delta between old and new function versions.
// patch_reverser restores the previous bytecode from patch_historikk.
// ressurs_grense enforces cpu_kvote (instruction count), minne_kvote (bytes), and fil_kvote.
// kvote_overskredet terminates the script and fires kvote_melding without crashing the host.
// api_versjon lets the host evolve the exposed API while maintaining api_kompatibilitet.
// live_konsoll provides an interactive REPL inside a running sandbox.
// konsoll_flerlinjet accumulates partial input until the expression is syntactically complete.
// wasm_sandbox wraps a WebAssembly module as an alternative isolation boundary.
// wasm_minne_delt maps a portion of host memory into the Wasm linear memory.

// Primitive flow:
// opprett sandbox: sandbox_opprett(konfig) -> ny VM-instans
//   -> bind innfødte via api_eksponér -> sett ressurs_grenser
// kjør script: script_kompiler(kilde) -> feil? -> kompiler_feil_samler -> returner feil
//   -> sandbox_kjør(bytekode) -> observer cpu/minne -> kvote_overskredet? -> avbryt
// hot_patch: patch_diff(gammel_fn, ny_fn) -> patch_anvend(patch_mål)
//   -> patch_historikk.push(gammel) -> VM peker nå på ny bytekode
// patch_reverser: patch_historikk.pop -> gjenopprett gammel bytekode
// live_konsoll: konsoll_kjør(uttrykk) -> kompiler -> kjør i sandbox
//   -> konsoll_resultat eller konsoll_feil -> vis i konsoll-panel
// wasm: wasm_modul_last(bytes) -> wasm_instans -> wasm_kall(fn, args)
//   -> wasm_grense_sjekk på minnetilgang

// This defines the scripting sandbox: isolated VM, resource quotas, hot-patch,
// live console REPL, and WebAssembly sandboxing.

