// Semantic direction:
// xr_system wraps OpenXR and WebXR behind a single API for VR, AR, and MR applications.
// xr_referanserom defines the coordinate origin (local, stage, or unbounded).
// enkelt_pass_stereo renders both eyes in one draw call using view instancing.
// foveasert_rendering uses eye-tracking data to render the fovea_senter at full resolution
//   and reduce ytre_resolution_faktor toward the periphery, saving GPU time.
// kontroller_sikt_pos is the virtual pointer ray origin for UI interaction in VR.
// kontroller_haptikk sends a vibration pulse to the physical controller.
// håndsporings provides skeletal joint poses without physical controllers.
// klype_deteksjon recognizes a pinch gesture between thumb and index finger.
// romlig_ankre pins a virtual object to a real-world position that persists across sessions.
// ar_plan_detektor finds horizontal and vertical surfaces in the real world (tables, walls).
// ar_bilde_detektor recognizes printed markers and returns their 3D pose.
// stråle_kast fires a ray from the controller tip into the scene to hit-test UI and geometry.
// teleportasjon moves the player's xr_referanserom to prevent physical locomotion sickness.
// vignett_bevegelse darkens screen edges during artificial movement to reduce VR sickness.
// snap_rotasjon turns the view in discrete snap_vinkel increments instead of smoothly.

// Primitive flow:
