// Semantic direction:
// reaktiv_strøm is a lazy, composable sequence of values over time following Reactive Extensions.
// strøm is cold by default — execution starts only when abonnent subscribes.
// bytt_kart cancels the previous inner strøm when a new value arrives — good for search.
// utmatt_kart queues inner strøm values and processes them sequentially.
// flat_kart subscribes to inner strøm concurrently, merging all outputs.
// scan_strøm applies an accumulator function and emits each intermediate result.
// buffer_strøm collects values into lists of buffer_antall, or within buffer_tid windows.
// vindu_strøm produces nested strømer instead of lists, allowing further operators per window.
// kombiner_sist emits an array of the latest values whenever any source strøm emits.
// dele_ref converts a cold strøm to hot and reference-counts subscriptions.
// debounce_strøm emits a value only after debounce milliseconds of silence.
// throttle_strøm emits at most one value per throttle window.
// sample_strøm emits the latest value whenever a sampler strøm emits.
// prøv_med_forsinkelse resubscribes after increasing delays on error.
// atferdsemne replays the most recent value to new abonnenter immediately.
// replay_emne buffers the last replay_buffer_størrelse values for late subscribers.
// planlegger controls which thread or event loop operators and subscriptions run on.

// Primitive flow:
// søk-som-du-skriver: inndata_strøm
//   .debounce(300ms)
//   .distinkt_til
//   .bytt_kart(tekst -> http_get("/søk?q="+tekst))
//   .fang_feil(tilbakefall_verdi([]))
//   .abonner_på(planlegger_umiddelbart, fn(resultater) { oppdater_ui })
// polling: strøm_intervall(5000ms)
//   .flat_kart(_ -> hent_data())
//   .distinkt_til
//   .abonner_på(planlegger_asynk, fn(data) { buffer_oppdater(data) })
// websocket strøm: strøm_fra_hendelse(ws, "melding")
//   .kart_strøm(json_parse)
//   .filter_strøm(m -> m.type == "pris")
//   .buffer_tid(100ms)   // batch UI-oppdateringer
//   .abonner_på(planlegger_kø, fn(batch) { tegn_om(batch) })

