// Semantic direction:
// data_pipeline is a directed acyclic graph (DAG) of kilde, transformasjon, and mål nodes.
// dag_topologisk orders nodes so each runs only after its upstream dependencies complete.
// kilde_inkrementell reads only rows where vannmerke_kolonne exceeds the last recorded value.
// transform_berik fetches additional data from a lookup source and merges it into each row.
// transform_valider_etl applies valider_regler (not-null, range, pattern) to each row.
// valider_handling_karantene routes invalid rows to a separate mål for review without halting.
// strategi_upsert inserts new rows and updates existing ones matched by a natural key.
// batch_kontrollpunkt saves processing position so a restart resumes rather than replaying from start.
// strøm_behandling processes records continuously as they arrive with strøm_latens targets.
// nøyaktig_én_gang guarantees each record is processed and written exactly once end-to-end.
// sjekk_null_andel fails if the fraction of null values exceeds kvalitets_terskel.
// sjekk_referanseintegritet verifies foreign-key-like relationships between datasets.
// schema_evolusjon tracks how the data schema changes; bakoverkompatibel means old readers still work.
// node_metrikk exposes rader_inn/ut/avvist and behandlingstid per node for observability.
// pipeline_varsel fires when rader_avvist or quality failures exceed configured thresholds.

// Primitive flow:
// dag_kjør(kjøring_id): dag_topologisk -> kjør noder i rekkefølge
//   kilde_node: kilde_inkrementell -> SELECT WHERE ts > vannmerke -> batch rader
//   transform: for hvert batch: kart/filter/aggreger/valider
//     ugyldig: karantene | gyldig: send til neste node
//   mål_node: strategi_upsert -> skriv batch til DB -> kontrollpunkt_lagre(vannmerke)
// feil midt i pipeline: gjenopprett fra kontrollpunkt -> les noder allerede fullført
//   -> hopp over fullførte -> fortsett fra siste kontrollpunkt
// datakvalitet: etter transformasjon: sjekk_null_andel(kolonne, terskel=0.01)
//   > terskel: kvalitets_rapport + handling_varsle | handling_avvis pipeline

// This defines the data pipeline and ETL: DAG execution, incremental extraction,
// transformation with validation and enrichment, upsert strategies, checkpointing,
// stream processing, data quality rules, and schema evolution.

