// Semantic direction:
// iam is the unified identity and access management layer for Norscode applications.
// oidc implements OpenID Connect on top of OAuth 2.0 for federated authentication.
// flyt_pkce (Proof Key for Code Exchange) protects public clients from code interception.
// id_token is a signed JWT containing the authenticated user's claims.
// tilgangs_token is a bearer token presented to resource servers to prove authorization.
// nonce ties the id_token to a specific authentication request, preventing replay attacks.
// saml_påstand is a signed XML document asserting the user's identity and attributes.
// påstand_vilkår restricts when and where the assertion is valid (audience, time window).
// saml_acs_url is the Service Provider endpoint that receives the SAML response.
// code_verifier is the random secret; code_challenge is its SHA-256 hash sent in the auth request.
// token_introspeksjon lets resource servers verify a token's validity with the authorization server.
// mfa_totp generates time-based one-time passwords using HMAC-SHA1 (RFC 6238).
// fido2_attestasjon verifies the authenticator's provenance; godkjenning verifies login assertions.
// abac (Attribute-Based Access Control) evaluates policy_regel against abac_attributt values.
// pbac_policy is a declarative policy document (similar to AWS IAM policy JSON).
// jit_provisjonering creates a local account on first login from the identity provider.
// deprovisjonering disables accounts when removed from the directory or IdP group.

// Primitive flow:
// oidc innlogging: klient -> autoriserings_endepunkt(scope, nonce, state, code_challenge)
//   bruker autentiserer hos IdP -> omdirigering med autoriserings_kode
//   klient -> token_endepunkt(kode, code_verifier) -> id_token + tilgangs_token
//   valider: signatur, utløp, nonce, audience
// saml: SP sender AuthnRequest -> IdP -> bruker logger inn -> saml_påstand sendes til acs_url
//   SP validerer signatur + vilkår -> opprett økt
// mfa: etter passord -> sjekk mfa_metode
//   totp: bruker oppgir kode -> mfa_verifiser(kode, hemmelighet) -> tidsvindu ±30sek
//   fido2: generer utfordring -> enhet signerer -> godkjenning.verifiser(svar)
// policy_evaluer(subjekt, handling, ressurs): samle attributter
//   evaluer alle matchende regler -> effekt_tillat | effekt_nekt (nekt vinner)

// This defines IAM: OIDC/OAuth2 flows with PKCE, SAML assertions, MFA with FIDO2/TOTP,
// attribute-based access control, and directory synchronization with JIT provisioning.

