// Semantic direction:
// gis is the Norscode spatial data module for geographic computation and visualization.
// wgs84 is the standard geodetic coordinate system used by GPS (longitude/latitude in degrees).
// projeksjon_transform converts coordinates between EPSG-coded reference systems.
// polygon_hull is a list of interior rings that cut holes in the polygon.
// geohash_kode encodes a lat/lon pair into a compact base-32 string for spatial indexing.
// geohash_nabo returns the adjacent cells in 8 directions for radius queries.
// h3_celle is Uber's hexagonal hierarchical index; h3_oppløsning controls cell size.
// rtree is a spatial tree that efficiently finds objects intersecting a bounding box.
// rtree_nærme_nabo returns the K closest geometries using incremental nearest-neighbor search.
// buffer_geo creates a polygon at a fixed avstand_meter around a geometry.
// konveks_skall is the smallest convex polygon enclosing a set of points.
// ch_ruting uses Contraction Hierarchies for sub-millisecond route queries on large graphs.
// turn_begrensning encodes prohibited maneuvers (no U-turn, no left turn) in the ruting_graf.
// spørring_isokrone returns the reachable area within a given travel time or distance.
// mvt_flise is a Mapbox Vector Tile: a compact binary format for serving map layers.
// wmts_protokoll serves georeferenced raster_fliser using a tile grid standard.
// geocode_adresse resolves a text address to coordinates; reversgeocode does the reverse.

// Primitive flow:
// romlig spørring: finn alle butikker innenfor 2 km fra punkt(10.75, 59.91)
//   buffer_geo(punkt, 2000m) -> polygon
//   rtree_søk(begrensningsboks(polygon)) -> kandidater
//   for hvert kandidat: er_innenfor(kandidat.geom, polygon) -> filtrer
//   -> sorter etter avstand_geo -> returner liste
// ruting: ruting_graf.bygg(kart_data, profil_bil)
//   dijkstra_geo(start, mål) | ch_ruting(start, mål) -> rute_resultat
//   rute_segment per vei -> instruksjon per sving -> returner til klient
// kart fliser: forespørsel GET /fliser/14/8234/4201.mvt
//   dekode flise_koordinat(x=8234, y=4201, zoom=14) -> begrensningsboks
//   spørring_boks(bbox) -> geometrier -> klipp til bbox -> kode som mvt_flise
//   flise_cache_geo(nøkkel) -> cache treff? server direkte
// h3: punkt_til_celle(lat, lon, oppløsning=9) -> celle_id
//   h3_nabo(celle_id, ring=1) -> 6 naboer -> samle alle for radius-spørring

// This defines spatial GIS: coordinate systems, geometry operations, spatial indexing
// with R-tree and H3, routing with contraction hierarchies, map tiles, and geocoding.

