// Semantic direction:
// vektor_db stores high-dimensional embedding vectors and enables approximate nearest-neighbor search.
// vektor_samling groups related vectors; each has fixed dimensjoner and a likhets_metrikk.
// hnsw_indeks is the Hierarchical Navigable Small World graph — the dominant ANN algorithm.
// hnsw_m controls graph connectivity; higher M improves recall but uses more memory.
// hnsw_ef_konstruksjon controls build quality; hnsw_ef_søk controls query-time exploration.
// ivf_indeks clusters vectors into nlist Voronoi cells; nprobe controls how many cells to search.
// pq_komprimering divides the vector into sub-vectors and quantizes each with learned sentrioder.
// flat_indeks is exact brute-force search — used for small collections or as a ground-truth baseline.
// ann_tilbakekalling is the fraction of true nearest neighbors returned; higher ef_søk improves it.
// filtrert_søk restricts candidates by metadata_filter before or after ANN search.
// pre_filter reduces the candidate set first (fast but lower recall); post_filter re-ranks after ANN.
// hybrid_søk_vdb combines vektor_søk with BM25 text search using alpha_hybrid weighting.
// maksimale_marginale_relevans selects results that are relevant but diverse (low inter-result similarity).
// flermodalitet searches across text, images, and audio in a shared embedding felles_rom.
// clip_embedding encodes both text and images in the same vector space (OpenAI CLIP).
// binær_kvantisering reduces 32-bit floats to 1 bit per dimension — 32× compression.
// tenant_isolasjon ensures namespace data cannot leak between tenants in a shared cluster.

// Primitive flow:
// sett inn: tekst_til_vektor("Norscode er et programmeringsspråk") -> [0.12, -0.34, ...]
//   sett_inn_vektor(samling, id, vektor, metadata={kilde:"dok1"})
//   hnsw_indeks: legg til node -> koble til M nærmeste naboer per lag
// ann_søk(k=5): query_vektor = tekst_til_vektor("programmeringsspråk")
//   hnsw: start fra øverste lag -> grådig descent til lag 0 -> ef_søk utforskning
//   returner k nærmeste med avstand og metadata
// hybrid_søk: ann_søk(vektor, k=100) -> bm25_søk(tekst, k=100)
//   alpha_hybrid: score = alpha * vektor_score + (1-alpha) * bm25_score
//   omrangering(topp 20) -> mmr(lambda=0.5) -> returner diverse topp 5
// filtrert: metadata_filter({kategori: "sport"}) -> pre_filter: reduser kandidatsett
//   ann_søk innenfor filtrert sett -> kombiner nøyaktighet og filterselektivitet

// This defines the vector database: HNSW and IVF-PQ indexes, filtered and hybrid search,
// MMR diversity, cross-modal embeddings, binary quantization, and multi-tenant namespaces.

