// Semantic direction:
// innebygd_system targets microcontrollers with no OS, limited RAM, and no dynamic allocation.
// linker_skript defines flash_region, ram_region, and stack_region memory layout.
// vektor_tabell is the array of interrupt_vektor function pointers at a fixed flash address.
// reset_handler is the first code that runs; it initializes BSS to zero and copies .data to RAM.
// ingen_std disables the Norscode standard library; ingen_alloc disables the heap allocator.
// minnekart_io maps peripheral registers to fixed memory addresses for memory-mapped I/O.
// bump_allokator is the simplest allocator: advance a pointer; free all at once.
// pool_allokator_innebygd pre-allocates fixed-size blocks, enabling O(1) alloc without fragmentation.
// gpio_pin represents one physical I/O pin configured as input or output with optional pull resistor.
// pin_interrupt fires a callback on a kant_stigende, kant_fallende, or kant_begge transition.
// uart_dma transfers bytes via Direct Memory Access, freeing the CPU during serial transfer.
// spi_modus defines clock polarity (CPOL) and phase (CPHA) for SPI peripheral compatibility.
// i2c_skriv_les performs a write followed by a repeated-start read in one atomic transaction.
// pwm_syklus is the duty cycle (0–100%) controlling average output power.
// capture_compare measures pulse widths or generates precise timing events via timer hardware.
// kritisk_seksjon disables avbrudd to protect shared state from concurrent interrupt handlers.
// minne_barriere prevents the compiler and CPU from reordering memory operations.
// modus_deep_sleep cuts most clocks and retains only key wakeup logic, minimizing power draw.
// rtos_integrasjon wraps FreeRTOS or Zephyr primitives behind a Norscode API.
// kontekst_bytte saves/restores CPU registers when the RTOS scheduler switches rtos_oppgave.

// Primitive flow:
// oppstart: vektor_tabell[1] = reset_handler
//   reset_handler: null_initialisering(BSS) -> data_kopiering(flash->RAM) -> main_innebygd
// gpio blink: pin_konfig(LED, retning_utdata) -> loop: pin_toggle(LED) -> forsinkelse(500ms)
// uart motta: uart_aktiver_interrupt -> avbrudd_handler: byte = uart_motta()
//   -> ring_buffer.push(byte) -> behandle i hoved-løkke
// i2c sensor: i2c_skriv_les(addr=0x48, reg=[0x00], les=2)
//   -> [msb, lsb] -> temperatur = (msb << 8 | lsb) * 0.0625
// pwm motor: pwm_konfig(kanal, frekvens=20kHz) -> pwm_syklus(kanal, 75%)
//   -> motor kjører på 75% effekt
// strømstyring: utfør måling -> send over UART -> modus_deep_sleep
//   -> vekke_kilde = tidtaker (hvert 10sek) -> gjenta

// This defines the hardware abstraction layer for embedded systems: startup, memory layout,
// GPIO, UART/SPI/I2C, timers, PWM, interrupts, critical sections, power modes, and RTOS integration.

