// Semantic direction:
// formell_verifisering mathematically proves properties of programs before or during execution.
// forutsetning is the precondition a caller must satisfy; etterforhold is what the callee guarantees.
// invariant holds across all executions; loop_invariant holds before and after each iteration.
// type_refinement adds a refinement_predikat to a base type (e.g. Heltall where self > 0).
// bevis_forpliktelse is a proof obligation the verifier must discharge to accept a refinement.
// avhengige_typer let types depend on values, enabling length-indexed lists and bounded integers.
// lineær_type ensures a resource is used bruk_én_gang — prevents double-free and use-after-free.
// borrow_sjekker enforces that lån references don't outlive the owned value.
// levetid_begrensning ensures a borrowed reference is valid for at least a given levetid_type.
// effekt_system tracks computational effects (IO, exceptions, state) in function type signatures.
// ren_funksjon has no effekter — always returns the same output for the same input.
// total_funksjon terminates on all inputs (no infinite loops, no unhandled exceptions).
// kripke_struktur is the state-transition model; CTL/LTL formulas describe temporal properties.
// bmc_grense is the depth bound for Bounded Model Checking — finds bugs within N steps.
// symbolsk_kjøring explores multiple execution paths simultaneously using smt_variabel inputs.
// smt_sjekk determines if a smt_formel is satisfiable; smt_modell witnesses a solution.
// lemma is a proved helper fact; teorem is the main result; qed marks proof completion.
// rv_monitor checks properties at runtime against an rv_spor of program events.

// Primitive flow:
// kontrakt_sjekk (kjøretid): kall fn(x)
//   sjekk forutsetning(x) -> brudd: kast kontrakt_brudd
//   kjør fn -> sjekk etterforhold(resultat) -> brudd: kast kontrakt_brudd
// refinement type: type PositivtHeltall = Heltall where self > 0
//   bevis_forpliktelse: vis at alle konstruksjoner tilfredsstiller predikatet
//   smt_sjekk(formel: x > 0) -> smt_modell gir moteksempel eller bevist
// symbolsk kjøring: ersatt inndata med smt_variabler -> kjør program symbolsk
//   ved grening: legg til begrensning per gren -> utforsk begge
//   ved assert: smt_sjekk(negasjon av assert) -> tilfredsstillbar: feil funnet
// ltl formel: □(forespørsel → ◇svar) — alltid: hvis forespørsel, til slutt svar
//   modell_sjekker: traverser kripke_struktur -> finn brudd-sti eller bevis

// This defines formal verification: design-by-contract, dependent/linear/effect types,
// CTL/LTL model checking, bounded model checking, SMT solving, proof assistants, and runtime monitoring.

