// Semantic direction:
// vitenskapelig_beregning provides numerical methods for solving continuous mathematical problems.
// ode_system is a set of coupled first-order ODEs: dy/dt = f(t, y).
// rk45 is the Dormand-Prince adaptive Runge-Kutta method with error control via rk45_toleranse.
// stive_system has eigenvalues with very different magnitudes; implicit methods like rosenbrock are needed.
// crank_nicolson_ode is second-order accurate and unconditionally stable for diffusion equations.
// grense_dirichlet specifies the function value on the boundary; grense_neumann specifies the derivative.
// cfl_betingelse (Courant-Friedrichs-Lewy) constrains the time step for explicit PDE stability.
// finite_element decomposes the domain into nett_elementer; stivhetsmatrise is assembled from local matrices.
// formfunksjon interpolates solution values within an element from nodal values.
// gauss_punkt provides the quadrature points and vekter for numerical integration within elements.
// quad_romberg uses Richardson extrapolation to achieve high-order accuracy from trapezoidal sums.
// brent_metode combines biseksjon, sekant, and inverse quadratic interpolation for robust root finding.
// l_bfgs is a limited-memory quasi-Newton optimizer for high-dimensional unconstrained problems.
// nelder_mead is a derivative-free simplex optimizer for noisy or non-smooth objectives.
// butterworth_filter has maximally flat frequency response with no ripple in either pass or stop band.

// Primitive flow:
// rk45 ODE: ode_funksjon(t, y) = [-y[0], y[0]-y[1]] (predator-prey)
//   ode_løser(rk45, f, y0=[10,5], t_span=[0,50], toleranse=1e-6)
//   adaptiv tidssteg: estimer lokal feil -> hvis > tol: halvér dt -> prøv på nytt
//   -> ode_verdier(N×2 matrise) ved ode_tidspunkter
// diffusjons PDE: ∂u/∂t = α∇²u, grense_dirichlet(u=0 på kanter)
//   fd_skjema: u[i,n+1] = u[i,n] + α*dt/dx² * (u[i+1,n] - 2u[i,n] + u[i-1,n])
//   sjekk cfl: α*dt/dx² ≤ 0.5 -> stabilt
// FEM Poisson: assembler_global(nett) -> stivhetsmatrise K, lastvektor f
//   løs: K*u = f via sparse_løs(K, f) -> u[noder]
// rot-finning: f(x) = x³ - x - 2, søk i [1, 2]
//   brent_metode: konvergerer til x=1.5214 på 7 iterasjoner

// This defines scientific computing: adaptive ODE solvers (RK45/Rosenbrock), finite differences
// and finite elements for PDEs, Gaussian quadrature, root finding with Brent, and L-BFGS optimization.

