// Semantic direction:
// kompilator_frontend transforms source text into a typed AST ready for semantic analysis.
// kilde_spenn records the byte range [start, slutt) in the source file for every AST node.
// lekser_modus handles context-sensitive lexing (e.g. strings disable operator recognition).
// leksem_kikk returns the next token without consuming it, enabling LL(1) parsing decisions.
// feil_gjenopprettelse allows the parser to continue after an error by discarding tokens.
// feil_synkronisering advances to the next statement boundary after panikk_modus is entered.
// inkrementell_parsing reuses unchanged AST subtrees when the user edits only part of a file.
// node_hash fingerprints each AST node's content; unchanged hash ⟹ gjenbruk_node.
// reparsér_område identifies the minimal source region affected by an edit.
// stabil_node_id assigns persistent IDs to AST nodes so language server references survive edits.
// diagnose_melding carries source positions and secondary markings for rich IDE error display.
// retting_forslag provides machine-applicable corrections (replace/insert/delete) for common mistakes.
// ast_lambda represents an anonymous function; it desugars to a named ast_funksjon_def internally.
// panikk_modus is entered on an uventet_leksem; the parser skips to a safe synchronization point.

// Primitive flow:
// leksing: kilde_tekst -> lekser -> leksem_kø
//   identifikator: les tegn mens alfanumerisk -> sjekk nøkkelord_tabell
//   heltall: les siffer -> konverter til i64
//   streng: modus_streng -> akkumuler til lukke-" -> modus_normal
// parsing (rekursiv nedstigning):
//   parse_funksjon: eat(tok_fn) -> navn(tok_ident) -> params -> blokk
//   parse_blokk: eat(lbrace) -> [parse_stmt]* -> eat(rbrace) -> ast_blokk
//   parse_uttrykk: Pratt parser -> nud/led per token_type -> bygger AST
// inkrementell: bruker endrer linje 42 -> reparsér_område([40..45])
//   les leksemer i område -> reparsér berørte stmts -> sammenlign node_hash
//   uendret noder: gjenbruk_node -> kun berørte noder er nye

// This defines the compiler frontend: context-sensitive lexer, Pratt expression parser,
// error recovery with panic mode, full AST node types, incremental reparsing with node hashing,
// and rich diagnostics with fix suggestions.

