// Semantic direction:
// bioinformatikk processes DNA, RNA, and protein sequences for genomic research.
// fastq_kvalitet stores per-base phred_score quality values alongside sequence data.
// phred_score Q = -10 log₁₀(p_feil); Q30 means 1 error per 1000 bases.
// needleman_wunsch finds the optimal global_justering with gap_åpning and gap_utvidelse penalties.
// smith_waterman finds the optimal local_justering — best local similarity regardless of ends.
// blosum62 is the most-used amino acid substitusjon_matrise for protein similarity searches.
// cigar_streng encodes an alignment compactly: "10M2I5M" means 10 matches, 2 inserts, 5 matches.
// posisjon_vekt_matrise models the probability of each nucleotide at each position in a motif.
// blast_e_verdi is the expected number of random hits with equal or better score — lower is more significant.
// fm_indeks uses the bwt (Burrows-Wheeler Transform) for compressed full-text search in O(m) time.
// bwa_algoritme aligns short DNA reads to a referanse_genom using BWT-based inexact matching.
// pileup stacks all read bases at each genomic position for variant_kalling.
// snp is a single nucleotide polymorphism; indel is a short insertion or deletion.
// tpkm normalizes RNA-seq expression for both transcript length and sequencing depth.
// differensiell_uttrykk identifies genes with statistically different expression between conditions.
// ld_beregning measures linkage disequilibrium — non-random association of alleles at nearby loci.
// gwas (Genome-Wide Association Study) tests each snp for association with a phenotype.

// Primitive flow:
// sekvens_justering: needleman_wunsch(seq1, seq2, blosum62, gap_åpning=-11, gap_utvidelse=-1)
//   dynamisk programmering: fyll (len1+1)×(len2+1) matrise
//   tilbakesporing: -> cigar_streng + justerings_score
// blast_søk: del spørring i kmer_størrelse=11 ord -> slå opp i blast_database (fm_indeks)
//   for hvert treff: utvid justering -> beregn blast_score -> filtrer blast_e_verdi < 0.001
// kortlesing_justering: bwa_algoritme(reads.fastq, referanse_genom.fa)
//   -> sam_format utdata -> sort + indekser -> bam_format
//   pileup per posisjon -> variant_kalling(snp/indel) -> vcf_format
// rna_seq: justeringskart -> tpkm per gen
//   deseq2_model(behandling vs kontroll) -> fold_endring + p_justert per gen
//   differensiell_uttrykk: p_justert < 0.05 og |fold_endring| > 2

// This defines bioinformatics: FASTA/FASTQ/BAM/VCF I/O, Needleman-Wunsch/Smith-Waterman
// alignment, BLAST search with FM-index, short-read alignment (BWA), variant calling,
// RNA-seq expression analysis, and GWAS.

