// Semantic direction:
// nett_simulering models network behavior in discrete time for protocol research and testing.
// sim_topologi defines the graph of nett_noder and nett_lenker.
// lenke_kø_disiplin determines how packets are scheduled when a link is congested.
// kø_codel (Controlled Delay) actively manages queue length to reduce bufferbloat.
// kø_red (Random Early Detection) probabilistically drops packets before the queue fills.
// pakke_ttl_sim counts hops; packets are droppet when it reaches zero.
// ospf_sim uses link-state advertisements to build a shortest-path ruting_tabell.
// bgp_sim exchanges path-vector bgp_annonsering between autonomous systems.
// mønster_poisson_nett generates inter-arrival times from an exponential distribution.
// mønster_burst models bursty traffic with alternating mønster_on_off periods.
// feil_omorden delivers packets out of the original sequence to test protocol robustness.
// nett_partisjoner splits the network so segments cannot communicate.
// bbr_algoritme (Bottleneck Bandwidth and RTT) congestion control measures bandwidth proactively.
// sack (Selective Acknowledgment) allows TCP to acknowledge non-contiguous received data.
// netem is the Linux kernel's network emulator for injecting controlled impairments in tests.
// nett_namespace isolates a network stack for each simulated process.
// chaos_nett injects tilfeldig_partisjon, forsinkelse, and tap during integration tests.

// Primitive flow:
// topologi setup: opprett 3 rutere, 6 verter -> lenker med forsinkelse=10ms, tap=0.01%
//   ospf_sim: alle rutere annonserer linker -> konvergér ruting_tabeller
// trafikk: trafikk_generator(mønster_poisson, last=100Mbps) -> send pakker
//   per pakke: ruting_tabell oppslag -> forward til neste_hopp -> lenke kø
//   kø_codel: mål køforsinkelse -> > 5ms: dropp pakke
// protokoll_test: injeksjon_feil(tap=5%, jitter=20ms) -> kjør tcp_klient
//   observer: retransmission_rate, tcp_vindu-størrelse, gjennomstrøm_sim
//   congestion_control: slow_start -> congestion_avoidance -> bbr_algoritme
// chaos_nett: tilfeldig_partisjon mellom DC-1 og DC-2 i 30sek
//   observer: applikasjon fallback til replika -> gjenopprettings_tid

// This defines network simulation and protocol testing: configurable topologies, queue
// disciplines, routing protocols (OSPF/BGP), traffic generators, fault injection, TCP
// congestion control analysis, and chaos engineering for networks.

