// Semantic direction:
// register_allokering maps unlimited virtual registers to finite physical registers.
// live_interval spans from a register's def_punkt to its last bruk_punkt.
// liveness_analyse computes which registers are live_inn and live_ut at each basic block.
// lineær_scan_ra sorts live intervals by start and greedily assigns registers.
// utkast_lengs_slutt evicts the interval with the furthest endpoint to free a register.
// spill_split divides a long interval at a profitable split_posisjon to reduce spill cost.
// rematerialisering re-computes a value instead of spilling/reloading if it's cheaper.
// interferens_graf has one node per virtual register; an edge means they're live simultaneously.
// fargelegging assigns colors (registers) such that no two adjacent nodes share a color.
// koalesering merges the src and dst of a copy instruction if they don't interfere.
// george_koalesering is safe if every neighbor of src is either low-degree or already colored.
// forforenkling iteratively removes low-degree nodes from the graph until only spill candidates remain.
// avhengighets_dag captures data/anti/output dependencies between instructions.
// kritisk_sti is the longest chain of dependent instructions; it determines minimum schedule length.
// listplanlegger iteratively selects the highest-priority ready instruction per cycle.
// latens_skjul schedules independent instructions between a load and its first use.
// superscalar_bredde is how many instructions can issue per cycle (e.g. 4 on modern OOO CPUs).
// register_presser estimates how many live ranges compete for registers at each program point.

// Primitive flow:
// liveness: bakovergående dataflyt: live_ut[B] = ∪ live_inn[suksessorer]
//   live_inn[B] = brukt[B] ∪ (live_ut[B] - def[B])
// lineær scan: sorter intervaller etter start -> for hvert intervall:
//   utløp aktive intervaller < start -> frigi registre
//   ledig register? -> tildel | ingen: utkast_lengs_slutt -> spill_slot
// interferens_graf: for hvert par (vr1, vr2): hvis begge live på samme punkt -> legg til kant
//   forforenkling: fjern lav-grad (<= K) noder til stack
//   tilordne: pop stack -> tildel farge som ikke brukes av naboer | ingen: spill
// instruksjon_planlegging: bygg avhengighets_dag -> kritisk_sti_beregn
//   listplanlegger: per syklus: velg alle klare instruksjoner med høyest prioritet (kritisk_sti_lengde)
//   -> utsteder inntil superscalar_bredde instruksjoner

// This defines register allocation and instruction scheduling: liveness analysis, linear scan
// and graph coloring allocators with coalescing, spilling with rematerialization, dependency
// DAG construction, list scheduling for superscalar pipelines, and register pressure estimation.

