// Semantic direction:
// algebraiske_effekter separate computational effects from pure logic using typed operasjoner.
// effekt_håndterer_alg interprets an effekt by providing a håndterer_klausal per operasjon.
// håndterer_fortsettelse is the delimited continuation — calling it resumes the computation.
// effekt_rad is the open row of effects in a function's type; rad_tom means the function is pure.
// poly_effekt allows functions to be polymorphic over their effect row (like row polymorphism).
// effekt_stat models mutable state as an effekt: stat_les reads and stat_sett writes.
// effekt_ikke_det models non-determinism: velg_en returns one result, velg_alle returns all.
// algebraiske_datatyper are the foundation of Norscode's type system for modeling domain data.
// sum_type (tagged union) represents "either A or B"; produkt_type (struct) represents "both A and B".
// phantom_type carries a type parameter that doesn't appear in the runtime representation.
// mønster_matching_alg deconstructs ADT values and binds their fields to variables.
// uttømmende_sjekk verifies at compile time that all variants are covered in a match.
// redundant_gren warns when a match arm can never be reached given prior arms.
// newtype wraps a primitive in a distinct type to prevent accidental mixing (e.g. Meter vs Second).
// opak_type hides the internal representation from external modules, exposing only a public API.
// mu_type is the fixed-point type constructor enabling recursively defined types.
// fold_type and unfold_type convert between the recursive and expanded representations.

// Primitive flow:
// effekt_kjør_alg: kjør uttrykk med effekt_rad [Stat[Int], Log]
//   håndterer Stat: stat_les -> les fra ref-celle | stat_sett -> skriv til ref-celle
//   håndterer Log: log_skriv -> legg til i buffer
//   effekt_løft_alg: wrap underliggende effekt i større rad
// mønster matching: match liste {
//   [] -> 0
//   [x] -> x
//   [x, ..rest] -> x + sum(rest)
//   } -> uttømmende_sjekk: alle varianter dekket
// newtype: type Meter = Meter(Desimal)
//   newtype_wrap(5.0) -> Meter(5.0)
//   kompilerer feil: Meter + Sekund -> type mismatch
// velg_alle: effekt_ikke_det { velg_en([1,2,3]) + velg_en([10,20]) }
//   -> [11, 21, 12, 22, 13, 23] (alle kombinasjoner)

// This defines algebraic effects and ADTs: typed effect rows with delimited continuations,
// built-in state/exception/nondeterminism effects, exhaustive pattern matching, newtypes,
// opaque types, and recursive types with fold/unfold.

