// Semantic direction:
// llvm_integrasjon uses LLVM as the code generation and optimization backend for Norscode.
// llvm_kontekst owns all LLVM state; one per compilation thread to allow parallel compilation.
// llvm_modul is the top-level container for functions, globals, and type declarations.
// llvm_funksjon_type describes the parameter and return types for a call signature.
// llvm_gep (GetElementPointer) computes a pointer to a struct field or array element.
// llvm_phi merges values from different predecessor basic blocks — the SSA join point.
// llvm_alloca reserves stack space; pass_mem2reg promotes alloca'd variables to SSA registers.
// pass_sroa (Scalar Replacement of Aggregates) splits structs into independent scalar variables.
// pass_gvn (Global Value Numbering) eliminates redundant computations across basic blocks.
// pass_licm (Loop Invariant Code Motion) hoists invariant instructions before loop headers.
// pass_vectorize auto-vectorizes loops using LLVM's SLP and loop vectorizer.
// opt_3 enables aggressive inlining, vectorization, and loop transformations.
// opt_s optimizes for binary size; opt_z minimizes size even more aggressively.
// calling_convention_fast allows the compiler to pass more arguments in registers.
// dwarf_kompilerings_enhet links object file sections to source file paths for debuggers.
// debug_lokasjon attaches source line/column to each LLVM instruction for gdb/lldb support.

// Primitive flow:
// Norscode IR -> LLVM IR:
//   for hvert ir_funksjon: llvm_funksjon(navn, llvm_funksjon_type)
//   for hvert ir_instruksjon: emit tilsvarende llvm_instruksjon
//   SSA phi-noder: ir_phi -> llvm_phi med samme inndata-par
// optimalisering: llvm_optimalisér(modul, opt_2)
//   function_pass_manager: mem2reg -> sroa -> gvn -> licm -> vectorize
//   module_pass_manager: inliner -> dead_global_elim -> globaldce
// native kode: llvm_kompilér(modul, mål_triple) -> objektfil
//   linker: ld / lld -> binær
// debug: emit dwarf_kompilerings_enhet -> debug_lokasjon per instruksjon
//   -> gdb: breakpoint på kilde_linje -> treffer riktig llvm_instruksjon

// This defines LLVM integration: IR type system, full instruction set, function attributes,
// calling conventions, the optimization pass pipeline (mem2reg through vectorization),
// and DWARF debug info generation.

