// Semantic direction:
// avansert_makro extends the macro system with full hygiene, quasi-quotation, and compiler introspection.
// hygiene prevents generated identifiers from accidentally capturing user-defined bindings.
// binder_mark stamps each introdusert_binder with a syntaks_kontekst so same-name bindings are distinct.
// alpha_rename resolves hygiene by renaming introduced bindings to fresh names during expansion.
// spann_def_site uses the macro definition's scope for hygienisk identifiers.
// spann_call_site uses the caller's scope for uhygienisk identifiers (deliberate capture).
// quasi_quote builds token streams using template syntax: quote! { fn #name() -> #ret { #body } }.
// unquote_makro splices a runtime token stream into a quasi_quote template at the # splice point.
// ctx_type_info lets a procedural macro query the type checker during expansion.
// ctx_resolve_sti checks whether an identifier resolves to a known path in the current module.
// metavar_expr matches any expression in a deklarativ_makro pattern.
// rep_separator allows repetition patterns to require a separator token (e.g. comma between items).
// derive_motor drives the automatic generation of trait implementations from struct/enum definitions.
// derive_enum_data provides the variant list with their fields for derive macros on enums.
// derive_generics exposes the generic type parameters so derives can propagate constraints.
// makro_feil_span attaches the error message to a specific source span for precise IDE highlighting.

// Primitive flow:
// quasi_quote: makro produserer
//   quote! { impl Vis for #navn { fn vis(&self) -> Tekst { format!("{:?}", self) } } }
//   -> token_strøm med hygieniske identifiers merket med def_site
// derive Lik: derive_input -> derive_struct_data -> fields = [("x", Heltall), ("y", Heltall)]
//   for hvert felt: generer `self.x == other.x`
//   bygg impl: quote! { impl Lik for #navn { fn lik(&self, other: &#navn) -> bool { #felt_sammenligninger } }}
// hygiene: makro definerer la x = 5 (introdusert_binder)
//   bruker kaller makro i scope med egen x: ingen konflikt
//   binder_mark(x, def_site) ≠ binder_mark(x, call_site) -> alpha_rename til x_42
// diagnose: makro mottar ugyldig input -> makro_feil_span(spann_av(token), "forventet heltall")
//   kompilator viser pilen på riktig token i IDE

// This defines advanced macros: full hygienic expansion with def/call-site spans, quasi-quotation
// with unquote splicing, procedural macro compiler introspection, declarative patterns with
// metavariables and separators, and a derive engine for struct/enum code generation.

