// Semantic direction:
// spesialisering generates type-specific versions of generic functions for performance.
// generisk_instansiering binds all type_parameter_binding values to create a concrete version.
// monomorfe_funksjoner have no runtime type dispatch — all types are known at compile time.
// boxing_eliminasjon removes heap allocation for values that don't need to be type-erased.
// flatet_layout inlines small struct fields directly into the enclosing allocation.
// delvis_evaluering specializes a function on its statiske_argumenter, producing a residual for the dynamiske ones.
// online_del_eval specializes incrementally as values become known; offline_del_eval requires full static analysis first.
// binding_tid_analyse classifies each argument as statisk (known at compile time) or dynamisk.
// polytypisme writes one function that operates over any type structure by case-splitting on type_rep.
// generisk_traversal visits every field of any ADT generically, without knowing the concrete type.
// handler_fusjon merges adjacent effekt_håndterer to avoid repeated stack manipulation overhead.
// handler_eliminasjon removes effect handlers when the contained computation provably uses no effects.
// sløyfe_peeling executes the first iteration(s) separately to enable invariant specialization.
// hot_cold_splitting separates rarely-executed branches into separate functions for better cache utilization.
// kloning duplicates a function at each call site with caller-specific specialization.
// kode_blåsing is the trade-off cost of spesialisering — more instances means larger binary.
// polyvariant_analyse tracks multiple possible types per variable for more precise specialization.

// Primitive flow:
// generisk fn sum<T: Additiv>(liste: Liste<T>) -> T:
//   kall sum([1,2,3]: Liste<Heltall>) -> spesialiser T=Heltall
//   instansierings_cache[(sum, Heltall)] finnes? -> gjenbruk | opprett ny versjon
//   sum_heltall: ingen boxing, direkte heltall-addisjon, SIMD-vektorisert
// delvis evaluering: fn http_send(metode: Tekst, url: Tekst, kropp: Bytes) ->
//   statiske: metode="GET" -> spesialisert get_fn(url) uten metode-sjekk
// handler_fusjon: fn bereg() med [Stat, Log] effekter
//   to separate handlers -> fused_handler som håndterer begge i én passering
// hot_cold_splitting: fn behandle(feil: Bool) { if feil: sjelden_sti() else: rask_sti() }
//   -> behandle_rask() med sjelden_sti i egen kald funksjon

// This defines specialization-based code generation: generic instantiation with caching,
// monomorphization, boxing elimination, partial evaluation with binding-time analysis,
// polytypism, effect handler fusion and elimination, loop peeling, and clone-based
// call-site specialization.

