// Semantic direction:
// gradert_typeteori annotates every variable binding with a grad indicating how many times it may be used.
// grad_null means the value is never used (erased); grad_én means used exactly once; grad_omega means unrestricted.
// lineær_ressurs must be used bruk_én_gang_gtt — neither dropped nor duplicated without explicit handling.
// afin_ressurs may be used at most once — it can be dropped but not duplicated.
// relevant_ressurs must be used at least once — it cannot be silently discarded.
// ressurs_split creates two lower-grade uses from one higher-grade source, e.g. sharing a file handle.
// lån_gtt borrows access to a resource without transferring ownership.
// type_eksklusivt_lån is a mutable borrow — no other borrows may coexist.
// levetid_parameter tags borrows with the scope in which the resource remains valid.
// outlives_relasjon 'a outlives 'b means the resource with lifetime 'a is valid for at least as long as 'b.
// forbruk moves a value, preventing further use; slipp destroys it, running the destruktor.
// dobbel_drop_feil is a compile error when the drop_sjekker detects a resource might be freed twice.
// kapabilitet_attenuation grants a subset of permissions — a read capability from a read/write one.
// objekt_kapabilitet uses values-as-capabilities for fine-grained access control.
// kanal_protokoll encodes the expected communication sequence in the channel's type.
// protokoll_dual is the mirror protocol — if one end sends, the other receives.
// destruktiv_oppdatering rewrites a lineær_ressurs in-place, consuming and producing a new version.

// Primitive flow:
// lineær ressurs: fn åpne_fil(sti) -> Fil[1]  -- fil brukes nøyaktig én gang
//   fn les_og_lukk(f: Fil[1]) -> Bytes
//     la innhold = fil_les(f)  -- f forbrukt her
//     fil_lukk(f)              -- kompileringsfeil: f allerede brukt
// korrekt: fn les_og_lukk(f: Fil[1]) -> (Bytes, Kvittering)
//   la (f2, innhold) = fil_les_lineær(f)  -- f forbrukt, f2 er ny lineær handle
//   la kvittering = fil_lukk(f2)          -- f2 forbrukt
// kapabilitet: fn behandle(ctx: NetCtx[les]) -- kan kun lese, ikke skrive
//   kapabilitet_attenuation(read_write_cap) -> read_cap -- nedgrad tillatelse
// kanal: protokoll P = !Heltall.?Tekst.End  -- send int, motta tekst, avslutt
//   protokoll_dual(P) = ?Heltall.!Tekst.End  -- server-siden

// This defines graded type theory and linear resources: usage annotations (0/1/ω), linear/affine/
// relevant types, ownership with destructors and drop checking, lifetime-parameterized borrows,
// object capabilities with attenuation, and session-typed channel protocols.

