// Semantic direction:
// effekt_polymorfisme lets functions be parametric over their effect rows — like type polymorphism for side effects.
// rad_variabel_ep is a type variable ranging over effect rows, enabling poly_effekt_type.
// rad_reordering allows effects in a row to be listed in any order — {Stat, Log} = {Log, Stat}.
// rad_duplikat handles duplicate effects in a row by unifying or rejecting based on the algebra.
// inferens_regel_generalisering closes over free rad_variabel_ep in a function's type at let-binding.
// verdi_begrensning prevents premature generalization of mutable references (as in ML).
// rad_unifikasjon solves constraints between effect rows by finding a substituting_ep.
// occur_sjekk prevents infinite effect rows like ε = {Stat | ε}.
// rad_differanse computes the effects remaining after a handler removes some from the row.
// poly_handler is an effect handler that works over any row containing the handled effect.
// lokal_effekt is an effect introduced and fully handled within one scope — not visible to callers.
// effekt_kovariant: a function with fewer effects is a subtype of one requiring more.
// hindley_milner_ep extends classic HM with row variables and effect constraints.
// begrensnings_generering collects effect constraints during type-checking of each expression.
// begrensnings_løsning applies unification and solves remaining constraints using the rad_løser.
// effekt_elision allows omitting effect annotations when they can be fully inferred.
// reader_effekt models read-only environment access; writer_effekt models append-only output.
// scope_effekt is introduced by a dynamic binding and handled at the end of its scope.

// Primitive flow:
// polymorf funksjon: fn kjør[ε](f: () -> [ε] Heltall) -> [ε] Heltall = f()
//   ε er rad_variabel_ep -> f kan ha hvilken som helst effekt
//   kall: kjør(fn() -> [Stat, Log] 42) -> effekt rad = {Stat, Log}
// inferens: la f = fn() { stat_les(); log_skriv("x") }
//   begrensnings_generering: f : () -> [{Stat}, {Log}]
//   rad_union: [{Stat}, {Log}] -> {Stat, Log}
//   generalisering: f : ∀ε. () -> [{Stat, Log | ε}]
// effekt_subtyping: fn ren() -> [] Heltall er subtype av fn() -> [Log] Heltall
//   kan bruke ren der Log-funksjon forventes (ingen effekter er subset av Log)
// rad_unifikasjon: {Stat | ε₁} = {Log, Stat | ε₂}
//   løsning: ε₁ = {Log | ε₂}
// lokal_effekt: fn bereg() -> [] Heltall {
//   håndter State { ... } i { stat_sett(0); les_og_øk() }
//   -- State er lokal, synlig ikke utenfor
// }

// This defines effect polymorphism and row-type inference: row variables, reordering, Hindley-Milner
// extended with effect constraints, row unification with occur check, effect subtyping, polymorphic
// handlers, local effects, and built-in polymorphic effect patterns (Reader/Writer/State/Gen/Scope).

