// Semantic direction:
// heterogen_beregning dispatches massively parallel work to GPUs and accelerators.
// hb_backend selects the compute API: Metal (macOS), Vulkan (cross-platform), CUDA (NVIDIA).
// kommandokø records GPU commands in en buffer for asynchronous submission.
// buffer_kart gives the CPU a pointer into GPU-accessible memory for zero-copy writes.
// kjerne_program is the compute shader compiled from kjerne_kilde (WGSL, HLSL, or GLSL).
// kjerne_dispatch specifies the three-dimensional grid of thread groups to launch.
// tråder_per_gruppe is the local workgroup size; tråd_id_hb is the thread's position within it.
// simd_bredde_hb (warp/wavefront) is the hardware SIMD lane count — threads execute in lock-step.
// gruppelokal_buffer is fast on-chip shared memory shared within one tråd_gruppe.
// barriere_gruppe synchronizes all threads in a group before they may proceed.
// memfence prevents memory operation reordering across the barrier.
// shuffle_hb exchanges values between threads in a warp without going through shared memory.
// prefix_sum (scan) computes cumulative sums efficiently across a thread group.
// atomisk_cas_hb (compare-and-swap) enables lock-free coordination between GPU threads.
// staging_buffer is a CPU-writable buffer used as an intermediary for dma_overføring.
// nullkopi_hb maps the same physical memory to both CPU and GPU address spaces.

// Primitive flow:
// matrix multiply: allokér buffer(A), buffer(B), buffer(C)
//   buffer_last_opp(A_data) -> buffer_last_opp(B_data)
//   kjerne_kompiler(matmul.wgsl) -> kjerne_dispatch(M/8, N/8, 1)
//   hvert tråd: les A_tile + B_tile til delt_minne -> barriere_gruppe
//   -> beregn C_tile via punkt-produkter -> skriv til buffer(C)
//   kø_vent -> buffer_les_ned(C)
// prefix_sum: dispatch(N/64 grupper, 64 tråder)
//   fase 1: last blokk til delt_minne -> scan lokalt -> skriv blokk-sum
//   fase 2: scan blokk-sums globalt -> scatter til output

// This defines heterogeneous computing: GPU context/queue management, buffer lifecycle,
// compute kernels with thread/group indexing, shared memory with barriers, warp shuffles,
// GPU atomics, and async DMA transfers via staging buffers.

