// Semantic direction:
// heap_kompaktering moves live objects together to eliminate fragmentation.
// header_forwarding_adresse is written into an evacuated object so surviving references can be updated.
// lisp2_tre_passeringer is the classic three-pass algorithm: mark, compute forwarding addresses, update+move.
// lisp2_beregn computes new addresses by scanning live objects and tracking the free pointer.
// lisp2_oppdater rewrites every pointer to its new forwarding address.
// sliding_kompaktering moves live objects toward the start of the heap without changing their relative order.
// pinned_objekt cannot be moved (e.g., it's referenced by native code); leaves gaps in the compacted region.
// regionbasert_kompaktering divides the heap into regions; only evacuation-worthy regions are compacted.
// work_stealing_kompakt distributes region compaction tasks across kompakt_tråder dynamically.
// nan_boxing encodes different value types in the NaN bit patterns of a 64-bit float.
// nan_boxing_float: the full 64-bit IEEE 754 value when the exponent is not all-ones.
// nan_boxing_int: store 32-bit integer in the low bits with a quiet-NaN marker.
// nan_boxing_peker: store a 48-bit pointer with tag bits indicating it's a heap reference.
// komprimert_peker stores heap pointers as 32-bit offsets from heap_base, halving pointer size.
// soa_transform converts array-of-structs to struct-of-arrays for better SIMD locality.
// fragmenterings_ratio is (heap_size - live_bytes) / heap_size; high values trigger compaction.

// Primitive flow:
// lisp2 kompaktering:
//   fase 1 mark: mark reachable objects -> sett mark_bit
//   fase 2 beregn: scan heap lineært -> beregn ny adresse for hvert live objekt
//     -> lagre ny_adresse i header_forwarding_adresse
//   fase 3 oppdater: scan alle pekere i heap + roter
//     -> erstatt gammel_adresse med ny_adresse
//   fase 4 flytt: kopier hvert objekt til sin ny_adresse -> oppdater fri_peker
// nan_boxing sjekk: verdi: uint64
//   bits[51..62] == alle-1 (quiet NaN marker)?
//     bits[63] == 0 og tag == 001: 32-bit heltall i bits[0..31]
//     bits[63] == 0 og tag == 010: heap-peker i bits[0..47]
//     bits[63] == 1: boolsk
//   ellers: standard float64
// parallell: del heap i N regioner -> tildel til N tråder
//   hvert tråd: kompaktér sin region uavhengig -> barrier -> slå sammen

// This defines heap compaction: LISP2 three-pass, sliding compaction with pinned objects,
// parallel region-based compaction, NaN-boxing value encoding, compressed pointers, and
// struct-of-arrays transformation for cache efficiency.

