// Semantic direction:
// container_runtime creates and manages isolated process environments using Linux primitives.
// cr_backend selects the runtime: runc (standard), crun (fast C), gVisor (userspace kernel), Kata (VM).
// container_bilde is an OCI image: a stack of immutable bilde_lag unified by overlayfs.
// lag_union presents all layers as a single merged_dir using copy_on_write_fs.
// oci_spesifikasjon is the OCI Runtime Specification JSON describing the container's full configuration.
// oci_navnerom_spec declares which Linux namespaces to create (pid, net, mnt, uts, ipc, user).
// virtuell_ethernet is a pair of linked veth interfaces: one inside the container, one on the host.
// bro_nett bridges the host-side veth to the physical network or an overlay network.
// vxlan_id is the 24-bit network identifier for VXLAN overlay tunnels between hosts.
// vtep_enhet (VXLAN Tunnel Endpoint) encapsulates/decapsulates VXLAN packets.
// arp_proxy answers ARP requests on behalf of containers to avoid broadcast floods.
// cni_plugin configures the container's network namespace using the CNI standard interface.
// overlayfs layers the writable upperdir over read-only lowerdirs transparently.
// workdir_cr is the temporary directory overlayfs uses during copy-on-write operations.
// cgroup_hierarki places each container under a dedicated cgroup for cpu/memory/io/pid limits.
// multi_arch_bilde uses manifest_liste to select the correct bilde for the host architecture.

// Primitive flow:
// container_opprett(bilde, config):
//   bilde_pull hvis ikke lokal -> overlayfs_mount(lowerdir=lag_liste, upperdir=rw_lag)
//   oci_config generér -> navnerom_opprett(pid, net, mnt, uts)
//   cgroup opprett -> sett cpu_grense + minne_grense
//   cni_legg_til -> veth_par opprett -> sett ip_tildeling -> ruter til gateway
//   seccomp_last_profil -> capabiliteter_sett -> container_start(pid 1)
// container_stopp: send SIGTERM -> vent -> SIGKILL -> cgroup_slett
//   overlayfs_umount -> nett_rensing (cni_slett) -> navnerom_fjern
// overlay nettverk: container A → B (forskjellige noder)
//   A sender pakke -> vtep encap(vxlan_id, dst_ip=node_B_ip) -> UDP 4789
//   node B mottar -> vtep decap -> leverer til container B's nett_navnerom

