// Semantic direction:
// formell_semantikk defines the precise mathematical meaning of programming language constructs.
// liten_steg (small-step) semantics defines one reduction at a time, showing intermediate states.
// stor_steg (big-step / natural) semantics evaluates an expression directly to its value.
// reduksjons_kontekst specifies where the next reduction step occurs in a term.
// plugge_inn fills a hole in the evalueringskontekst with a term.
// normal_form is a term that cannot be reduced further; sitter_fast is a normal form that isn't a value.
// determinisme holds if at most one reduction step applies to any configuration.
// konvergens ensures computation eventually reaches a normal_form.
// lukking_verdi represents a function together with the environment binding its free variables.
// denotasjon assigns a mathematical object (set, function, domain element) to each term.
// cpo (Complete Partial Order) is the mathematical domain for modeling recursion and loops.
// fiksepunkt_teori finds the meaning of recursive definitions as the least fixed point.
// knaster_tarski guarantees existence of fixed points on CPOs via monotone function iteration.
// hoare_tripel {P} C {Q}: if P holds before C executes, Q holds after it terminates.
// wp_beregning (weakest precondition) computes the minimal precondition guaranteeing postcondition Q.
// separasjons_logikk extends Hoare logic with heap ownership for safe reasoning about pointers.
// stjernekonjunksjon (separating conjunction) asserts two heap predicates hold on disjoint heaps.
// frame_regel allows local reasoning: if {P} C {Q} then {P * R} C {Q * R} when C doesn't affect R.
// concurrent_separation_logic extends this to concurrent programs with race_condition_fri proofs.

// Primitive flow:
// liten_steg evaluering av (2+3)*4:
//   (2+3)*4 → (5)*4  [legg til regel: 2+3 → 5]
//   → 5*4            [evalueringskontekst: []*4]
//   → 20             [multiplikasjonsregel]
// hoare_tripel for while: {I} while b do C {I ∧ ¬b}
//   loop_invariant I: bevis I er sann ved start, bevares av C
//   wp(while b do C, Q) = sterkeste I slik at I ∧ b → wp(C, I) og I ∧ ¬b → Q
// separasjons_logikk: {x → 3 * y → 5} swap(x, y) {x → 5 * y → 3}
//   frame_regel: legge til vilkårlig R på begge sider -> lokalt resonnement
// denotasjonell: ⟦if b then e1 else e2⟧ρ = if ⟦b⟧ρ then ⟦e1⟧ρ else ⟦e2⟧ρ

// This defines formal semantics: small-step with evaluation contexts, big-step with closures,
// denotational semantics with CPO/fixed points, Hoare logic with weakest preconditions,
// and separation logic with the frame rule for heap reasoning.

