// Semantic direction:
// probabilistiske_strukturer trade exactness for dramatic reductions in memory and time.
// bloom_filter answers set-membership queries with no feil_negativ but possible feil_positiv.
// bloom_optimal_k = (bf_størrelse/n) * ln(2) minimizes the feil_positiv_rate for n elements.
// telling_bloom extends the bloom filter with increment/decrement counters to support bf_fjern.
// cuckoo_filter stores cf_fingeravtrykk values and supports deletion with lower feil_positiv_rate.
// cf_relocate kicks out an existing fingerprint and rehashes it to its alternate bucket.
// hyperloglog estimates the cardinality of a set using only O(2^p) bytes of hll_registre.
// hll_bias_korreksjon applies empirical corrections for small and large range edge cases.
// count_min_sketch estimates the frequency of any item using cms_dybde independent hash functions.
// cms_konservativ_oppdatering only increments counters that hold the current minimum, reducing error.
// skip_liste is a probabilistic alternative to balanced trees with expected O(log n) operations.
// reservoir_sampling maintains a uniform random sample of size k from a stream of unknown length.
// reservoir_l_algoritme (Li's L algorithm) samples efficiently with O(1) amortized updates.
// min_hash estimates Jaccard similarity between sets without materializing the sets.
// lsh (Locality Sensitive Hashing) groups similar items into the same lsh_bøtter for ANN search.
// misra_gries finds all elements with frequency > n/k using O(k) space.
// t_digest estimates quantiles (p95/p99) over a data stream with bounded error.

// Primitive flow:
// bloom: bf_størrelse = -n*ln(p)/ln(2)², bf_hash_antall = -log₂(p)
//   legg_til(element): for i in 0..k: bf_bit_array[hash_i(element) % m] = 1
//   sjekk(element): alle bits satt? -> sannsynligvis i sett | noen=0 -> definitivt ikke
// hyperloglog: hash(element) -> finn lengste løpende 0-sekvens
//   hll_registre[bucket] = max(hll_registre[bucket], lengde+1)
//   estimat = α_m * m² / Σ(2^(-reg[j]))
// count_min: inkrement(element): for i in 0..d: cms_hash_tabeller[i][h_i(element)]++
//   spørring(element): min over alle d hash-tabeller
